  <Docs>
    <summary><span data-ttu-id="fb199-101">指定序列化流中可以缺少一个字段，这样 <see cref="T:System.Runtime.Serialization.Formatters.Binary.BinaryFormatter" /> 和 <see cref="T:System.Runtime.Serialization.Formatters.Soap.SoapFormatter" /> 就不会引发异常。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fb199-101">Specifies that a field can be missing from a serialization stream so that the <see cref="T:System.Runtime.Serialization.Formatters.Binary.BinaryFormatter" /> and the <see cref="T:System.Runtime.Serialization.Formatters.Soap.SoapFormatter" /> does not throw an exception.</span></span></summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="fb199-102">此属性允许您指定 <xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.Formatters.Binary.BinaryFormatter> 或 <xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.Formatters.Soap.SoapFormatter>将忽略可序列化类型（应用 <xref:System.SerializableAttribute> 的类型）的新字段。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fb199-102">This attribute allows you to specify that new fields in a serializable type (a type to which the <xref:System.SerializableAttribute> is applied to) are ignored by the <xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.Formatters.Binary.BinaryFormatter> or the <xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.Formatters.Soap.SoapFormatter>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="fb199-103">这将为序列化数据的应用程序的旧版本创建的类型启用版本容错序列化。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fb199-103">This enables version-tolerant serialization of types created for older versions of an application that serializes data.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="fb199-104">例如，当格式化程序遇到不包含新字段的版本生成的流时，不会引发异常，并且旧类型上的现有数据将作为正常处理。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fb199-104">For example, when the formatters encounter a stream produced by a version that does not include the new fields, no exception is thrown, and the existing data on the older type is processed as normal.</span></span>  
  
 ]]></format>
    </remarks>
